# Implementation Plan - Phase 4: Real-Time Collaboration with Socket.IO and Yjs CRDT

This plan covers the implementation of real-time sync using Yjs (CRDT), Tiptap editor integrations, Socket.IO room handling, carets/cursors syncing, and debounced database updates.

## Proposed Package Additions (Frontend)
We will install the following packages in `frontend/`:
- `@tiptap/extension-collaboration` (Binds Tiptap document node structure directly to a Yjs Shared Type)
- `@tiptap/extension-collaboration-cursor` (Syncs caret positions, selection highlights, and user presence indicators within Tiptap)

---

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Components

#### [NEW] [documentSocket.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/backend/sockets/documentSocket.js)
Establish a centralized module mapping Socket.IO connection event triggers:
- `join-document`: Enforces access permission checking by querying MongoDB. Adds the client connection to the document ID's socket room.
- `document-change`: Receives Yjs state update vectors from a client. Broadcasts the update buffer to all other sockets in the same room.
- `save-document`: Accepts document string states. Performs debounced updates to the MongoDB document content to avoid DB query bottlenecks.
- `cursor-update`: Broadcasts cursor coordinates and name tag metadata.
- `disconnecting` / `disconnect`: Cleans up active user references.

#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/backend/server.js)
Import the `documentSocket` register method and bind it to the Socket.IO `io` server instance.

